        Mike Tigas is a developer, journalist, photographer, civic hacker, and security/privacy tinkerer. He works at ProPublica, is a core contributor to the Tor Project, and is an adjunct instructor at New York University.
        His work includes news applications, privacy software (Onion Browser), data tools (Tabula, CivOmega), talks & workshops, & lots of other good stuff.
        
        

        
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        
    

    



 

    

    
